description: Join the misadventures of Knuckles, El Ravager, Zayre and Teflon Billy as they wreak havoc with their unique brand of heroics. This issue re-tells the KoDT strips I Got a Rock, Let’s Make a Deal, Armload of Trouble, The Straight and Narrow, and Return to Muskeegie, from the perspective of their HackMaster role-playing game characters. This issue also includes the original Armload of Trouble as a backup KoDT strip!

This issue re-tells the KoDT strips Thor-Dude, An Overbearing Situation, Princess Kristina, and the Venus Elixir, from the perspective of their HackMaster role-playing game characters. This issue also includes the original Princess Kristina as a backup KoDT strip!

volume.name: Knights of the Dinner Table: Illustrated

description: Join the misadventures of Knuckles, El Ravager, Zayre and Teflon Billy as they wreak havoc with their unique brand of heroics. In this issue, our ‘heroes’ force a henchman into a dangerous situation to retrieve a piece of junk. But what will they do when the junk turns out to be a much sought-after magic item, turning their lowly servant into a charismatic lord? Can the Knights adapt to being followers instead of leaders? Or will they just kill him and get it over with? Find out in the newest episode, “Just for the Helm of It.” This issue also includes the original Just for the Helm of It as a backup KoDT strip!

volume.name: Knights of the Dinner Table: Illustrated

description: Now with tons of all new material! Join the misadventures of Knuckles, El Ravager, Zayre and Teflon Billy as they wreak havoc with their unique brand of heroics. In this issue, what began as some harmless looting and pillaging turns into a courtroom drama, as the Trio fight to win their freedom from a haughty judge and a noble lord - who just may give them more trouble than they bargained for. Can a dwarven thief really be a good lawyer? And who’s REALLY behind what’s happening to our heroes? Find out in the newest episode, “Judgment Day.” This issue also includes an excerpt from the original Judgment Day as a backup KoDT strip!

volume.name: Knights of the Dinner Table: Illustrated

description: Join the misadventures of Knuckles, El Ravager, Zayre and Teflon Billy as they wreak havoc with their unique brand of heroics. In this issue, the Trio journey through a forest labyrinth in search of a long-lost dungeon. Can our heroes survive the ancient depths of this unopened vault of horror? Will Knuckles ever recover from the loss of his leg? And are wild squirrels REALLY that hostile? This issue ties directly into the KoDT: Illustrated/Travelers crossover special #1 and Travelers #14. When laid side by side, these three issues connect to make one large cover!

volume.name: Knights of the Dinner Table: Illustrated

description: Join the misadventures of Knuckles, El Ravager, Zayre and Teflon Billy as they wreak havoc with their unique brand of heroics. In this issue, Knuckles suffers from depression... Can Zayre, El Ravager, and Teflon Billy possibly cheer him up? Or will the purchase of a (dangerous) replacement mount be just the cure? Find out in “Tales of the Dwarven Warhorse!”
name: Tales of The Dwarven Warhorse

volume.name: Knights of the Dinner Table: Illustrated

description: When the all-powerful gawds decide to hold a contest of champions, you'd think that neither the Untouchable Trio Plus One or the Travelers would be chosen ? and you'd be right. But when all the real heroes are dead, only these two troublesome groups have a chance to decide the outcome of the "Contest of the Gawds!" Join the havoc as the last worst choices for peace come together in one climactic battle to end all battles! This issue ties directly into the Knights of the Dinner Table: Illustrated/Travelers crossover (all three issues of which will ship the same week). When laid side-by-side, these three issues make one large cover!

volume.name: Knights of the Dinner Table Illustrated vs. Tony DeGerolamo's The Travelers

If you like stories about nice boys and girls doing nice things, then this isn't the book you're looking for: If you like to see teachers getting splatted with tomatoes, policemen being chased by gnashing dogs and grown-ups getting exactly what they deserve, then this is the book you're looking for! Join Dennis the Menace, Roger the Dodger, Minnie the Minx and The Bash St Kids in the best Beano Annual ever!

After releasing her first hit single, Airi is pleased to find out that she's been nominated for the Grand Prix Artist of the Year award. But this news sends reigning pop princess Selaca into a pique of jealous rage.

The unscrupulous singer orders her management company to nip Airi's blossoming career in the bud. There can only be one queen of pop and Selaca will stop at nothing to boot Airi off the hit parade!

description: A Godly King Makes a Deadly Choice. Josiah, the king of Judah, is alerted that the massive Egyptian army is marching across his land to help Assyria fight Babylon. Ignoring the advice of Iddo, his faithful advisor, Josiah attacks Pharaoh's army. As the king charges recklessly into battle disguised as a soldier, Iddo can only watch the vicious combat, fearing the worst and wondering what chain of events has been set into motion. Will Judah be crushed between the empires that surround it?
name: The Coming Storm

True-crime writer Phil Stanford tells a gritty tale from Portland’s underbelly.

Introducing the underbelly of Portland Oregon. Several story lines weave a tale about the gritty underworld.

description: The "Super Duper Comic Con" is in town and The Tick and Arthur are invited guests to this gala event! But it's The Tick who is swamped by scores of fans and TV producers while Arthur gets ignored as "just a sidekick." The Tick even meets the wrestler-turned-actor named 'The Gun Show' who has been chosen to portray him on a Tick TV series! With all of this attention directed towards The Tick, his envious super-hero friends - including even Arthur - contemplate expelling him from their super-team! Is it possible that Arthur also been bitten by the green-eyed-monster and has turned on The Tick? Could this be the beginning of a TV series for "The Tick" but the end for the duo known as "The Tick and Arthur?"

description: She's been forced to move out of Manhattan after her parents decided to get divorced, and is now living in a small town (who cares which one) with her mom and her aunt, Tanner. Not to mention the fact that she's dealing with being the new kid in school, many trips to the principal's office, first kisses, etc. But you know what? She's got her friends Reggie, Rhonda, and Pajamaman, and everything's going to be okay. Except, of course, when it isn't. In Jimmy Gownley's first original volume in two years, Amelia and company rise and fall through the ranks of nerd, geek -- and cheerleader? -- in a daring attempt to not be unpopular.
name: The Tweenage Guide to Not Being Unpopular
